description:
Plot Summary

In this pilot animated short, Finn is known as "Pen".

Pen and his best friend Jake have their first encounter with the Ice King, and save Princess Bubblegum for the first time.
name: Pilot

description:
Plot Summary

Princess Bubblegum tries to bring her candy people back from the dead, and accidentally turns them into zombies.
name: Slumber Party Panic

description:
Plot Summary

Lumpy Space Princess accidentally bites Jake, and infects him with the Lumps. The race is then on for Finn, LSP and Jake to travel to Lumpy Space in search of a cure, before Jake is turned into a Lumpy Space Person permanently.
name: Trouble in Lumpy Space

description:
Plot Summary

The Ice King takes Finn and Jake prisoner, after they accidentally stumble onto his land. He places them in a cell with a group of captured princesses, and together the gang plan their escape. But when Ice King freezes Jake, it is up to Finn to save everyone.
name: Prisoners of Love

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake are enjoying one of Tree Trunks's apple pies when she tells them about the legend of the crystal apple, the one thing she wants more than anything else in the world. They vow to help her find it, but with no previous adventuring experience, taking her along proves dangerous.
name: Tree Trunks

description:
Plot Summary

Jake invokes the wrath of a witch, who takes revenge by stripping him of his powers. Rather than apologise to her, he tries to find another way to get them back.
name: The Witch's Garden

description:
Plot Summary

Finn swears to get revenge when Jake plays a prank on him, and builds a pie throwing robot that will be able to throw pies at Jake forever. But the plan backfires when the machine is too clever.
name: What Is Life?

description:
Plot Summary

After discovering that he has an intense phobia of the ocean, Finn asks Jake to help him overcome his fear.
name: Ocean of Fear

description:
Plot Summary

When Finn tries to fight his way through a dungeon on his own, it isn't long before he realises how much he usually relies on Jake.
name: Dungeon

description:
Plot Summary

After an accident, Princess Bubblegum is left horribly disfigured - and it is the day of an important meeting of Ooo royalty! Convinced that the Duke of Nuts is responsible, a furious Bubblegum banishes him from the Candy Kingdom, vowing to hate him forever. But Finn and Jake know the truth.
name: The Duke

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake meet a giant creature named Donny, who is an obnoxious bully. They try to befriend him, encouraging him to change his ways - and in doing so, learn a hard lesson about the natural order in Ooo.
name: Donny

description:
Plot Summary

Marceline hires Finn as her personal henchman. But when some of the things she asks of him appear to conflict with his morals, he faces some tough decisions.
name: Henchman

description:
Plot Summary

It's a rainy day in Ooo, and Finn and Jake are bored. The bad weather means they can't go out adventuring as they usually do, so they decide to entertain themselves, using their imaginations. However, things soon begin to get out of hand.
name: Rainy Day Daydream

description:
Plot Summary

Princess Bubblegum asks Finn and Jake to capture the Ice King and bring him to her castle. When they get there, she asks them to guard their prisoner until she comes back, warning them to keep careful watch over him - but with no explanation as to why. In her absence, Ice King begins to protest his innocence, claiming to have committed no recent crimes, and pleads with them to set him free. This causes Finn and Jake to doubt themselves. Are they doing the right thing?
name: What Have You Done?

description:
Plot Summary

After stumbling across his legendary sword, Finn and Jake find the secret hideout of their hero, Billy. Billy is one of the most famous warriors in all of Ooo, but he has become jaded and renounced violence. As they worship Billy, Finn and Jake swear to do the same. but solving Ooo's problems in a non-violent way turns out to be a major challenge for the two friends.
name: His Hero

description:
Plot Summary

While out travelling, Finn and Jake learn of a mysterious monster named the Gut Grinder, who has been terrorising a group of small towns and stealing the residents' gold. The pair vow to retrieve the loot and fell the monster, but the more evidence they gather on the creature's identity, the more it seems that Jake is the real Gut Grinder.
name: Gut Grinder

description:
Plot Summary

When Marceline asks Finn to help her with a song, he soon realises that she has a troubled relationship with her father. Wanting to help, he summons Hunson Abadeer from the Nightosphere, and in doing so unleashes Adadeer's soul-sucking evil upon the Land of Ooo.
name: It Came from the Nightosphere

description:
Plot Summary

After days of adventuring without rest, Finn and Jake finally manage to get home to their beds. But their sleep is disturbed by a strange looking horse who won't stop staring at them.
name: The Eyes

description:
Plot Summary

After getting a particularly nasty splinter in his finger, Finn decides he needs some protection. He starts to wear a thimble as finger protection, but after a mysterious knight named Sir Slicer mocks his thimble, he decides to get himself some real armour.
name: Blood Under the Skin

description:
Plot Summary

Jake is sick, and in a bad mood. He decides that a story will cheer him up, but only a true story will do. Finn sets out to have an adventure he can go home and tell him about, but finds it is not easy to make his day interesting and suspenseful on purpose.
name: Storytelling

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake are alarmed when a giant snail gatecrashes their home. The snail is desperately lonely, and finds it impossible to talk to girls. The pair soon realise the only way to get rid of him is to help him find love.
name: Slow Love

description:
Plot Summary

Afraid of hurting those he cares about, Jake swears to never use violence again. But when Finn is then kidnapped and taken to the Crystal Dimension, there is nothing Jake can do to stop it.
name: Crystals Have Power

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake encounter a Tree Witch, who is in desperate need of some princess hair. She believes that she is only mean because she is ugly, and that if she could feel pretty like the princesses do, then she could find happiness and stop her evil ways. To achieve this, she captures Jake, refusing to let him go until Finn brings her some real hair from a genuine princess. Desperate to save his best friend, Finn travels all over Ooo in search of princess hair.
name: To Cut a Woman's Hair

description:
Plot Summary

While Ice King is at the hospital with Gunther, Jake and Finn search his lair, convinced he has kidnapped another princess - and are shocked to find that he has a secret collection of ninja artifacts and memorabilia.
name: The Chamber of Frozen Blades

description:
Plot Summary

The time has come for Jake to meet Lady Rainicorn's parents. When Finn reminds him of the war between rainicorns and dogs in the past, Jake becomes anxious that they will take an instant dislike to him because of his species. The two come up with a plan to try to pass Jake off as a fellow rainicorn, but will they believe the act?
name: Her Parents

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake accept a quest from a dying knight and are entrusted with three magic beans - two of which are good, while one is evil. But which is which?
name: The Pods

description:
Plot Summary

Having been invited to one of Princess Bubblegum's prestigious scientific gatherings, Finn becomes anxious about impressing her and appearing clever in front of the princess and her friends. He purchases a pair of glasses which have the power to bestow genius level intellect upon the wearer - but at what cost?
name: The Real You

description:
Plot Summary

Determined to beat one of their favourite video games, Jake and Finn convince BMO to teleport them inside of it, so they can play for real.
name: Guardians of Sunshine

description:
Plot Summary

Princess Bubblegum has an errand to run, and asks Finn and Jake to look after her princess plant while she is away. When the pair accidentally kill the plant, they travel to the realm of the dead - with some help from Peppermint Butler - to retrieve the plant's soul before the Princess returns.
name: Death in Bloom

description:
Plot Summary

On Finn's birthday, Jake takes him out for a special treat. But on the train journey there, as passengers begin to drop dead around them, the two find themselves caught up in a murder mystery.
name: Mystery Train

description:
Plot Summary

It's Couple's Night at the Ooo drive-in, and Finn has no one to go with. He invites Princess Bubblegum, and when she refuses, Jake comes up with a plan to change her mind. But once Marceline gets involved, Finn becomes confused by all the contradictory advice, and messes things up with the Princess.
name: Go With Me

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake awaken to find a monster roaming around in the Land of Ooo. When the creature eats them, they discover a colony of party bears living in the monster's stomach, but when they try to tell the bears where they are, they won't listen. After learning that the monster is going to eat lava from a nearby volcano, Finn and Jake try to convince the bears to stop partying and leave.
name: Belly of the Beast

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake are hanging out with Hot Dog Princess when her people send a message in the sky. When they go to investigate, the pair discover that there is a magical maze, and if they can reach the center then they will be granted one wish. With the help of some hot dog knights, they race to find the center of the maze - but their over reliance on Jake's stretching abilities soon takes its toll on his health.
name: The Limit

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake pay a visit to Marceline, with the intention of watching a movie together. While they are there, she and her friends convince the pair the have been turned into vampires.
name: Heat Signature

description:
Plot Summary

A race of tiny, adorable creatures named the Cuties are hellbent on taking over Ooo - but they are so small and fragile that they tire themselves out and fall apart when they try to fight. Realising that they pose no threat but will not leave until they have won a battle, Jake and Finn come up with a plan.
name: Conquest of Cuteness

description:
Plot Summary

A creature claiming to be Marceline's spirit guide asks Finn and Jake for help, after she accidentally casts a sleep spell on herself. The creature sends the pair into Marceline's mind to retrieve her memories and awaken her from endless sleep, but in doing so they come across some memories of a young man they don't know named Ash. But who is Ash, and what does he have to do with Marceline's problem?
name: Memory of a Memory

description:
Plot Summary

After trying to trick the Breakfast Princesses into drinking a love potion, the Ice King is grounded by Finn and Jake. In a temper, Ice King hires a hitman, but he takes the name too literally, believing the creature he has hired will only hit Finn and Jake. When he realises he has accidentally hired someone to kill them, it is up to the Ice King to save their lives.
name: Hitman

description:
Plot Summary

After her encounter with the Lich, Princess Bubblegum is now physically only 13 years old. When Lemongrab exploits this fact and claims rightful leadership of Ooo, she and Finn must do whatever it takes to get rid of him - even if it means Finn giving up everything he has always wanted.
name: Too Young

description:
Plot Summary

A story set in a gender swapped version of Ooo. Fionna is unsure whether Prince Gumball is interested in her as a girlfriend, or just a friend. After he invites her to attend a ball with him as his girflfriend, everything seems to made clear - but there is more to the situation than meets the eye.
name: Fionna and Cake

description:
Plot Summary

A Door Lord appears, and steals a number of sentimental items before sealing himself behind a magical door. An inscription on the door's frame proclaims that it can only be opened by the music of a genuine band - but can Finn, Jake, Princess Bubblegum and Marceline put aside their various personal issues and work together to get inside?
name: What Was Missing

description:
Plot Summary

Susan Strong and her people, the Hyoomans, are being terrorised by a group of mysterious creatures. She asks Finn and Jake for help, but Jake is not convinced, and insists that Susan is insane.
name: Beautopia

description:
Plot Summary

A snow golem finds a stranded fire wolf pup, after the pup's home is destroyed by fire. After some initial reluctance, he takes the pup into his own house, but the animal's powers are too destructive, and the snow golem's things are soon ablaze. He eventually decides to try and carry the pup to a safe place where he can be with his own kind - but will he make it in time before he melts entirely?

Meanwhile, Finn and Jake battle with the Ice King, who has fashioned himself an invincible suit of armour.
name: Thank You

description:
Plot Summary

Jake has a "croak dream": a dream featuring the Cosmic Owl which is supposed to foretell the dreamer's death. Finn is devastated by the idea of losing his friend, while Jake urges him to accept the inevitability of fate, and to find some comfort in the natural circle of life.
name: The New Frontier

description:
Plot Summary

While in the library studying rainicorns, Jake accuses Finn of making up adventures. Wandering around in the library while Jake tries to read, Finn meets a group of mysterious paper creatures - but will Jake believe him?
name: Paper Pete

description:
Plot Summary

After being told there is only one way to solve a problem, Finn becomes enraged, and sets out to prove everyone wrong. But he soon finds himself in a series of situations in which there appear to be only two possible courses of action. Will Finn resign himself to the natural way of things, or will he find another way?
name: Another Way

description:
Plot Summary

Finn is left heartbroken when he is rejected once more by Princess Bubblegum, and plunges into a desperate depression. In an attempt to cheer him up, Jake goes looking for another potential love interest for his best friend.
name: Incendium

description:
Plot Summary

When Tree Trunks befriends a local pig, it isn't long before the pair fall deeply in love with one another. After declaring their feelings, the two become inseparable - but their public displays of affection are met with revulsion by the other residents of Ooo.
name: Dream of Love

description:
Plot Summary

Finn and Jake wake up the Nightosphere with no recollection of how they got there. They make a plan to find Hunson Abadeer and find out the truth, but the Nightosphere is a treacherous place, and the task proves difficult.
name: Return to the Nightosphere

description:
Plot Summary

Marceline is ruling the Nightosphere - but wait, that's not right! Has her father done something to her to change her mind about taking on the family business? Jake and Finn won't rest until they get answers.
name: Daddy's Little Monster

description:
Plot Summary

After he is hugged by an alpha Hug Wolf, the residents of Ooo begin to make complaints about Finn. Can he really be the strange creature who is breaking into their houses and hugging them without their consent? And if so, what can he do to stop himself, before it is too late?
name: Hug Wolf

description:
Plot Summary

Tired of being rejected by princesses, Ice King decides to create one of his own.
name: Princess Monster Wife

description:
Plot Summary

Princess Bubblegum, becoming increasingly aware of her own mortality, decides to create a successor to her throne.
name: Goliad

description:
Plot Summary

After talking with Turtle Princess, LSP decides to write a salacious expose on how no man can resist her lumps - not even Finn. But when she poses as his secretary in order to get close to him, her plan takes an unexpected turn.
name: Gotcha!

description:
Plot Summary

When BMO and Lady Rainicorn won't play with him anymore, Jake tries to teach Finn how to play his favorite game: Card Wars. But as Finn gets better at the game, Jake becomes more and more volatile.
name: Card Wars

description:
Plot Summary

When his people become angered with him and come to take him back to Mars, Magic Man knows this will mean a trial, and possibly even a death sentence. In a desperate attempt to evade capture, he switches places with Jake, forcing the dog to take on Magic Man's physical form and ensuring that he will be taken to Mars in his place.
name: Sons of Mars

description:
Plot Summary

Princess Bubblegum is disturbed to learn that Finn and Flame Princess are dating. When she tries to break them up, Finn and Jake assume she is merely jealous - but ignoring her warnings could prove dangerous for everyone.
name: Burning Low

description:
Plot Summary

When one of Finn's socks goes missing, BMO is on the case, and plays detective while Finn and Jake are away.
name: BMO Noire

description:
Plot Summary

One of Princess Bubblegum's creations, the Earl of Lemongrab, has become wayward and unpredictable. After finding out that he has been sneaking into the Candy Kingdom at night, Bubblegum decides to try and find some company for him.
name: You Made Me
